{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase the State pension for all retired Armed Forces Veterans",
        "additional_details": "The basic state pension is only around \u00a37,000 a year. We the petitioners demand this is increased substantially for all Armed Forces Veterans, so that it covers all living costs, such as council tax, rent and utilities.\r\n\r\nEach year there is a surplus in the National Insurance fund of billions of pounds, and in 2020 the fund was in surplus by over \u00a335 billion.\r\n\r\nThis is more than enough to increase State pensions substantially for all our Armed Forces Veterans.\r\n\r\nWe owe them, \"BIG TIME\"",
        "background": "We the petitioners want the Government to provide adequate \u201cCradle to Grave\u201d care in the form of an increased State Pension for all retried Armed Forces Veterans, to ensure that they receive a State pension that covers all living costs on reaching retirement age.",
